div.div: fix(extra-natives/five): ensure damage packs don't desync on death or blood clear

tweak(error): support DumpServer-based FatalError for launcher
FatalError calls in the launcher would usually lead to a Win32 message box, even when the dump server is already initialized.
This changeset adds support for showing in this scenario as well.

tweak(client/launcher): better error handling for missing launcher DLLs
The error messages for CoreRT.dll, CitizenGame.dll, and the tlsDll not being able to load were a bit confusing, did not show error details, and would not verify game files either.

tweak(citizen-devtools): improve monitor performance
This will lessen the impact of the current Resource Monitor by removing a noticeable part of the ScRT pre- and post-run overhead.
Rundown of some changes:
* ResourceMonitor - Removed the `std::unordered_multiset`, really slow for what they do, notoriously so. - Repurposed the `tbb::concurrent_unordered_map` to take on the multiset's function. - Only uses a single stopwatch per resource. - Some branch prediction optimizations. - Proper and more performant math changes. - Use resource pointers as keys instead of strings. * String formatting is at least twice as slow as a simple concatenation.

tweak(net): rare m_impl race fix
I'm not sure if this happened, but some stacks looked suspect.
tweak(ext/cfx-ui): add a disclaimer for why the server feeds are missing from the community feed
tweak(ext/cfx-ui): make sentry ignore errors from the console
fix(ext/cfx-ui): make eos/eol warning link texts localize unconditionally

fix(vendor): update CEF to cfx-m103.2604
This includes citizenfx/chromium@1dd9a14ac352a8e2415d76312addd534d71d7f76 which fixes the regression reported on https://forum.cfx.re/t/4934989.
tweak(ext/cfx-ui): add fullscreen-ish media viewer for ActivityItem

fix(vfs): handle race condition safety
This is a changeset that was implemented a while ago but since there's some issues that may be explained by VFS race conditions in mpMenu it's time for it ti actually get added.

fix(game/five): enable the MSAA classification shader for 'graphics mods'
ENBSeries expects this to be called to have the 'TextureDepth' parameter work at night time, expecting the DepthBuffer texture to be passed as reductionDepthTexture to this shader.
tweak(ext/cfx-ui): allow more UI texts to be localizable
fix(ext/cfx-ui): handle empty or undefined strings in colorize fn
fix(gsclient): skip duplicates during localhost_sentinel DNS lookup

tweak(server): state bag replication and sync changes
* Any client that owns an entity can now create its replicating state bags on the server. * Clients will queue their state bag changes and send them after getting an ACK from the server (meaning the server now knows of the entity). * State bag updates to clients are now being sent after the clone creation packets. * State bag updates are not being sent to clients that just got a call to remove the associated entities.
